\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \~She was twelve years younger than he, tall and lovely, with sun-streaked hair and brown eyes that went dark and seemed to turn inward whenever she was pensive.\~}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 She was in the habit of analysing everything that affected her, drawing back from her emotions and inspecting them as if they were a clutch of strange insects she had discovered crawling on her skirt.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Peels of dead skin hung down from the shadows like torn veils of ectoplasm; ferns sprouted from the vanes, which were thicker than cathedral columns; swallows curved through the black air. Sometimes, lying with her hidden by a tuck of the wing, Meric would think the beating of their hearts was what really animated the place, that the instant they left, the water ceased flowing and the swallows vanished. He had an unshakable faith in the transforming power of their affections, and one morning as they dressed, preparing to return to Hangtown, he asked her to leave with him.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Her fingers trailed over his shoulder - a gentle, treasuring touch.\~}
